    <sect1>
        <title>Requirements</title>
        
   
    <para>
        The requirement documents define numbered requirements which are referred to in specification documents and bug reports. These documents are derived from several 
        sources including customer requests, regulatory requirements, product briefs, and good software engineering practice.
    </para>
    <para>There are two broad types of requirement documents: "platform" level requirements that cover general  requirements for all MedCommons products and product specifications.
        Each requirement document contains numbered requirements (the formal requirements) as well as use cases which define how the system or subsystem is to be used.
        </para>
